I'll start by executing the file reader tool to read the input data as the first step in our pipeline.

<tool_call>file_operations_reader
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            I'll execute the data_processing_validator tool to validate the data we read in the previous step. Since we don't have a specific schema, I'll use a default validation schema.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {
        "type": "object"
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {
    "data": {}
  },
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I'll execute the data_processing_transformer tool to transform the validated data, using JSON as both input and output format for simplicity.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            The transformation step failed with a timeout error. I'll try an alternative approach by first parsing the data before transformation. I'll execute the data_processing_parser tool to prepare the data for transformation.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

                        Now that the data is parsed, I'll retry the transformation step using the data_processing_transformer tool with the parsed data.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

The transformer expects XML input but we have JSON. I'll use the file_operations_converter tool to first convert the data from JSON to XML format before transformation.

<tool_call>file_operations_converter
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "xml",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

                        Now that we have the data in XML format, I'll retry the transformation step with the data_processing_transformer tool, specifying XML as the input format.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "xml",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
